<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[140,1804,473,902]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, C. W." box="[494,718,702,740]" journalOrPublisher="Quart. Journ. Taiwan Museum" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" pagination="23 - 32" part="3" refId="ref4111" refString="Chen, C. W. 1950: Systematic notes on the genera Orolestes and Psolodesmus (Odonata). Quart. Journ. Taiwan Museum, 3, (1), 23 - 32." title="Systematic notes on the genera Orolestes and Psolodesmus (Odonata)" type="journal article" year="1950">Chen (1950)</bibRefCitation>
the Formosan 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1904" box="[1017,1603,702,740]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Psolodesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorothea">
<emphasis box="[1017,1242,702,740]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">P. dorothea</emphasis>
Williamson (1904)
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a local race of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1870" box="[645,931,755,793]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Psolodesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandarinus">
<emphasis box="[645,931,755,793]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">P. mandarinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
MacLachlan which is found in South China and northern Formosa. It seems, therefore, to be reasonable to place 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oguma" authorityYear="1913" box="[1479,1656,810,848]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Psolodesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="mandarinus" subSpecies="kuroiwae">
<emphasis box="[1479,1656,810,848]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">kuroiwae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Oguma as another subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1870" box="[618,845,864,902]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Psolodesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandarinus">
<emphasis box="[618,845,864,902]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">mandarinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Chen supposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
